            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "In light of this issue, I've just spotted that `PyUnstable_SetImmortal` now exists. So that's the solution on 3.15+.\n\nI think I'll just disable it in 32 bit builds. It's a small optimization rather than something we genuinely have to do and the download numbers for 32 bit builds aren't high enough to justify anything else (for Cython at least... maybe everyone is using 32 bit Numpy...). And I'm not sure I even know how to test 32 bits any more locally.",
