            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think actually there's a subtle bug on 64 bit architectures as well. (size_t)refcnt > (size_t)UINT32_MAX is false, so you don't actually go into the overflow branch in `Py_SET_REFCNT` and `ob_tid` doesn't get reset:\n\nhttps://github.com/python/cpython/blob/f4f102027a9b0edc72a048f17b696aa92d2e6893/Include/refcount.h#L177-L188\n\nMaybe use the implementation from pythoncapi-compat?\n\nhttps://github.com/python/pythoncapi-compat/blob/75a796764d63327268d195e2d5c044e564d0dada/pythoncapi_compat.h#L2686",
